</span>Staffing Up
                </h2>
                <p>Mergers often adhere to tight timelines, placing pressure on the procurement team to produce rapid
                    results. This can stretch resources and restrict their ability to manage the intricacies of
                    combining procurement functions. When your company transitions to acquisition mode, consider
                    augmenting your existing team to maintain consistent support for internal stakeholders and ensure
                    smooth operations.</p>
