</span>Supporting Successful Integrations
                </h2>
                <p>M&A activities enable organizations to consolidate their supplier base, negotiate better terms, and
                    achieve economies of scale. By combining volumes, companies can gain leverage and greater influence
                    over suppliers which will result in better pricing, service levels, and contractual terms.</p>
                <p>Procurement can play a pivotal role in getting ahead of potential integration issues and ensuring the
                    procurement operating model is delivering maximum value by identifying shared goals between each
                    organization and creating a unified procurement strategy that aligns with the new organization’s
                    overall goals. At this point during the process, the focus should be on streamlining procurement
                    systems, standardizing processes, ensuring regulatory compliance, and leveraging best practices from
                    both organizations to produce greater efficiency.</p>
